OL,3,CMakerfield by-election: Declared
OL,4,Ccandidates and everything else you
OL,5,Cneed to know
OL,7,FThe current Mayor of Greater
OL,8,FManchester is Labour's candidate.
OL,10,FThe three-time mayor and former MP for
OL,11,FLeigh told ITV News: "I'm standing on
OL,12,Fa call for change, aren't I? I think
OL,13,Fwe need to change Labour to some
OL,14,Fdegree so we can change politics,
OL,15,Fchange the country."
OL,17,FHe added: "For me, we need a different
OL,18,Fpath that puts those things back under
OL,19,Fpublic control, makes them more
OL,20,Faffordable.
OL,26,@sD@VOUwD@TO]yD@KOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/25
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1780592748
OL,3,CMakerfield by-election: Declared
OL,4,Ccandidates and everything else you
OL,5,Cneed to know
OL,7,F"The path that Britain has been on for
OL,8,F40 years, in my view, has been the
OL,9,Fwrong path.
OL,11,F"It's taken us to this place where
OL,12,Fpeople can't afford life's basics,
OL,13,Fthey can't afford a few pints at the
OL,14,Fweekend, they can't afford a holiday.
OL,15,FAnd that's why they're saying to
OL,16,Fpoliticians, do better. This is not
OL,17,Fgood enough. And they're right to say
OL,18,Fthat.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/25
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1780592748
OL,3,CMakerfield by-election: Declared
OL,4,Ccandidates and everything else you
OL,5,Cneed to know
OL,7,F"I'm saying there's a new path here,
OL,8,Fnew politics to build a new economy
OL,9,Ffor Britain."
OL,11,F"That is the main question in this by-
OL,12,Felection. Are people happy to stick on
OL,13,Fthe path that Britain's been on for 40
OL,14,Fyears, or do we want a new path?"
OL,16,FDan Clarke (The Libertarian Party)
OL,18,FDan Clarke has been named as the
OL,19,Fcandidate for the Makerfield by-
OL,20,Felection.
OL,26,@qD@MO]sD@AOUvD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/25
